```

## Column Descriptions
| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `city` | string | Name of the city |
| `country` | string | Two-letter country code |
| `temperature_celsius` | float | Current temperature in °C |
| `feels_like_celsius` | float | "Feels like" temperature in °C |
| `humidity` | int | Humidity percentage (0–100) |
| `pressure` | int | Atmospheric pressure in hPa |
| `wind_speed` | float | Wind speed in meters per second |
| `weather_description` | string | Human-readable weather condition |
| `data_timestamp` | string | When the weather data was recorded (UTC) |
| `pipeline_run_date` | string | When the pipeline was executed (UTC) |

## Troubleshooting

| Problem | Solution |
|---|---|
| `401 Unauthorized` error | Your API key may still be activating. Wait 10 minutes and try again. |
| `KeyError` in transform.py | A field is missing from the record dictionary. Compare your code with the project instructions. |
| `ModuleNotFoundError` | Run `pip install requests pandas duckdb` to install missing packages. |
| `ImportError` on extract/config | Make sure all `.py` files are in the same `weather-etl` folder. |

## What I Learned
- How ETL pipelines function in practice — extracting, transforming, and loading data in stages
- Working with REST APIs and processing JSON responses
- Data transformation and cleaning with pandas (handling nulls, type casting, unit conversion)
- Storing and querying structured data with DuckDB and SQL
- Python module organization — defining functions in one file and importing them in another
- Error handling patterns that make pipelines resilient

